1. Hamstrings prime

Top Dumbbell Hamstring-Focused Exercises
1. Dumbbell Romanian Deadlift (RDL)

Slight bend in the knees.

Push hips back while keeping spine neutral.

Most effective dumbbell exercise for hamstrings.

2. Dumbbell Stiff-Leg Deadlift

Less knee bend than an RDL.

Increases stretch on the hamstrings.

Great for deep hamstring lengthening.

3. Dumbbell Good Morning (Dumbbells on Shoulders)

Hold dumbbells at your shoulders.

Hinge hips back.

Very hamstring-dominant, similar to barbell version.

4. Dumbbell Single-Leg RDL

One dumbbell or two.

Improves balance, gluteâ€“ham stability, and strength.

Excellent unilateral hamstring work.

5. Dumbbell Glute Bridge / Dumbbell Hip Thrust

Place dumbbell on hips.

Drive hips up while keeping shins vertical.

Hits the upper hamstrings + glutes.

6. Dumbbell Hamstring Slide (with Towels or Sliders)

Lie on your back, heels on towels on a smooth floor.

Hold a dumbbell on your pelvis for load.

Extend legs out and curl them back in â†’ hamstring curl pattern.

7. Dumbbell Leg Curl (Between Feet)

Lie face down or seated.

Hold a dumbbell between your feet and curl it up.

Surprisingly effective if done carefully.

8. Dumbbell Step-Back Lunge (Hamstring-Biased)

Big backward step.

Keep forward shin vertical.

Focus on hip hinge as you descend â†’ more hamstring engagement.

9. Dumbbell 45Â° Back Extension (with Dumbbell Hug)

If you have a back extension bench.

Hug a dumbbell and hinge over the pad.

Strong hamstring/hip hinge emphasis.

ðŸ’¡ Tips to Maximize Hamstring Activation

Focus on hip hinge movements (hips back, slight knee bend).

Think stretchâ€“loadâ€“contract: long hamstring stretch â†’ controlled lift.

Move slowly through the eccentric (downward phase).

